{
  "texts": [
    "In preliminary experiments, we found that the limited size of the database, containing ~ 10 3 examples of previously-reported (most of them stable) NADES, led to significant overfitting.",
    "In this case, the algorithm was able to obtain relatively high scores, even if predicting \"stable\" for non-stable mixtures.",
    "To address this problem, the uACL database was augmented by a script called Mixture Generator Alpha (uACl_mix_gen_alfa.py).",
    "The script is responsible for generating mixtures by randomly varying the number of components (from 3 to 5), varying each individual chemical component (among 198 possibilities), as well as the stoichiometric coefficient for each component (from 1 to 10).",
    "The mixtures generated by this strategy were labeled as \"0\" (unstable) and then added to the uACL database according to the number of data augmented (e.g."
  ]
}